The paper presents a method for improving the visualization of single-cell RNA sequencing data using t-SNE, a popular dimensionality reduction technique. This is a problem that is relevant to several areas of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG, stat.ML), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of t-SNE for visualizing gene expression patterns, which is relevant to the computational biology subfield of genomics (q-bio.GN).
